  "fun_facts": [
    "Widely used as CALCIUM SUPPLEMENT - gentler on the stomach than calcium carbonate",
    "Used in hospitals as emergency IV treatment for low calcium (hypocalcemia) and high potassium (hyperkalemia)",
    "Also an antidote for hydrofluoric acid burns - the calcium binds to fluoride ions",
    "Provides both calcium AND the chelating benefits of gluconic acid",
    "Better absorbed than some other calcium salts and doesn't cause GI upset",
    "The gluconate form makes it more bioavailable and palatable than calcium chloride or calcium carbonate"
